official_title: A bill to provide temporary authority for the Secretary of Agriculture to sell timber from the U.S. Forest Service lands in Alaska consistent with various acts.

summary.text: Authorizes the Secretary of Agriculture to enter into contracts through September, 1977 for the sale of timber from national forest lands in Alaska.

titles.title: A bill to provide temporary authority for the Secretary of Agriculture to sell timber from the U.S. Forest Service lands in Alaska consistent with various acts.
